  "summary": "## ATX Review — Issue #614 Hermes Multi-Provider Templates\n\n**Aggregate Rating: 2/5** — Three blocking issues across two specialists. Not mergeable.\n\n---\n\n### Blocking Issues\n\n| # | Specialist | Locat...",
  "feedback": "## ATX Review — Issue #614 Hermes Multi-Provider Templates\n\n**Aggregate Rating: 2/5** — Three blocking issues across two specialists. Not mergeable.\n\n---\n\n### Blocking Issues\n\n| # | Specialist | Location | Issue |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------|\n| B1 | security-reviewer | `render.py:442` + both config templates | **YAML key injection**: `role` from hosts.json copied into `AuxiliaryProviderInputs` without checking against `AUXILIARY_SLOTS`. Rendered as bare unquoted YAML key (`{{ _aux.role }}:`). The canonical sync caller (`lifecycle_canonical.py:538`) never calls `_pa.validate()`, so a crafted `\"role\": \"vision:\\n  malicious_key\"` in hosts.json injects arbitrary YAML into the remote config.yaml on `clawctl agent sync`. The legacy path is mitigated because it calls `_pa.validate()` before building overlays. |\n| B2 | test-coverage | `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py` | **No lockstep test**: AGENTS.md §\"Template lockstep\" explicitly requires that both legacy and canonical families produce structurally identical output for the same inputs. There is no test feeding any multi-provider scenario through both families and asserting parity. A field landing in only one family silently diverges — exactly the class of bug the rule was written to prevent. |\n| B3 | test-coverage | `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py` | **No canonical bedrock-aux test**: `_build_provider_env_views` lines 799–816 add a bedrock branch for auxiliary providers. This branch is exercised only by the legacy template test. No `TestCanonicalMultiProvider` test constructs `AuxiliaryProviderInputs(type='bedrock')`. A typo in the canonical template's bedrock-aux branch is invisible. |\n\n**Fix for B1 (one line):**\n```python\n# render.py:385, after the `role != 'primary'` guard\nfrom clawrium.core.provider_attachments import AUXILIARY_SLOTS\nif role not in AUXILIARY_SLOTS:\n    raise AgentConfigError(\n        f'auxiliary provider {aux_name!r} has invalid role {role!r}; '\n        f'expected one of {sorted(AUXILIARY_SLOTS)}'\n    )\n```\nAlso call `_pa.validate()` in `lifecycle_canonical.py` before `build_render_inputs` to make both paths defence-in-depth equivalent.\n\n---\n\n### Warnings\n\n| # | Specialist | Location | Issue |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------|\n| W1 | registry + lifecycle | `render.py:744-749` + both config templates | `_HERMES_DEFAULT_TITLE_GEN_MODEL` Python constant is **dead code** — never passed to templates. Both Jinja families carry their own inline copy. A model ID bump requires 3 independent edits; the Python constant silently drifts. Either delete it or promote it as a context variable to both templates and remove the inline Jinja dicts. |\n| W2 | registry | `hermes.env.j2:47-58` | Legacy env bedrock dedup **state-machine gap**: `_seen_type_keys.update()` is nested inside the credential-validity guard. If the primary bedrock attachment has empty creds, `'bedrock'` is never registered, and a subsequent aux bedrock attachment claims the slot — auxiliary wins instead of primary. Fix: move `_seen_type_keys.update()` unconditionally before the emission guard. |\n| W3 | registry | Both config templates | Auxiliary YAML key **ordering diverges** between legacy (insertion order from `config.providers`) and canonical (alphabetical sort by role at `render.py:451`). For 2+ aux providers, `configure` (Ansible) then `sync` (canonical) produces different bytes on disk. Sort `_explicit_aux` iteration in `hermes-config.yaml.j2` to match `render.py:451`. |\n| W4 | lifecycle | `render.py:431-436` | Ollama auxiliary endpoint **validated but silently discarded**: `build_render_inputs` raises `AgentConfigError` when ollama aux has no endpoint, but `AuxiliaryProviderInputs` has no `endpoint` field, so the validated value is thrown away. The templates emit no `base_url` for ollama aux. Decide the contract: if upstream aux slots don't support `base_url`, remove the false guard; if they do, add the field and emit it. |\n| W5 | security | `hermes.env.j2:80-84` | WARNING comment writes `_ctype` (from `config.providers`) verbatim. A `type` value containing `\\n` in providers.json breaks the EnvironmentFile line, allowing a new assignment line after the comment. Apply `| replace('\\n','') | replace('\\r','')` to `_ctype` in the WARNING loop. |\n| W6 | test-coverage | `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py:370-389` | No canonical env **single-provider back-compat test**. The env template restructured API key emission to the new `provider_env_views` loop. A regression producing a blank line or missing `HERMES_INFERENCE_PROVIDER` for ollama-primary would be invisible. Add a test asserting exactly the expected keys and no `WARNING` lines for a single-provider render. |\n| W7 | test-coverage | `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py` | No canonical test for **multiple auxiliary roles** (only one `AuxiliaryProviderInputs` with `role='vision'` is ever constructed). An off-by-one in the Jinja for-loop dropping a second role would not be caught. |\n| W8 | test-coverage | `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py` | No **role-collision test** (two aux entries with same role). Both families silently last-win; neither behavior is asserted. The uniqueness contract deferred to `validate()` has no enforcement test. |\n\n---\n\n### Suggestions\n\n| # | Location | Note |\n|---|----------|------|\n| S1 | `render.py:382-384` | Role not validated against `AUXILIARY_SLOTS` (partially overlaps B1 — the fix for B1 closes this too). |\n| S2 | `render.py:744-749` | `_HERMES_DEFAULT_TITLE_GEN_MODEL` is dead code — overlaps W1. |\n| S3 | `test_render.py` (missing) | Add direct unit tests for `_build_provider_env_views` and `_build_aux_yaml_views` as pure functions, independent of template rendering, to separate Python logic bugs from Jinja bugs. |\n| S4 | Both config template families | Ollama-as-aux emits `provider: \"custom\"` with no `base_url`. Verify against `NousResearch/hermes-agent hermes_cli/config.py:716-795`. If unsupported, raise `AttachmentError` in `build_render_inputs` for `ollama` aux type. |\n| S5 | PR / CHANGELOG | Document that all existing single-provider hermes agents will gain `auxiliary: title_generation: model: ...` in `config.yaml` on next `configure`/`sync`. Note the model IDs in `_default_title_gen_map` were verified against hermes-agent vX.Y.Z. |\n\n---\n\n### What's Clean\n\n- `shq`/`yq` filter coverage: all secret values (api_key, AWS triplet) are quoted in both template families. ✅\n- WARNING comments emit only the provider type name — no key value leakage. ✅\n- Secrets loaded exclusively from secrets.json via `_clean_secret`→truthiness; no hosts.json credential reads. ✅\n- Ansible extra-vars passed as a structured dict — no `shell=True` or f-string injection risk. ✅\n- `build_render_inputs` handles missing secrets gracefully (no `KeyError`); primary always registered before auxiliaries. ✅\n- Conflict detection covers Bedrock (AWS triplet compare). ✅\n- `AuxiliaryProviderInputs` fields typed correctly. ✅\n- Explicit `title_generation` suppresses the per-primary-type default (Python path logic is correct). ✅\n\n---\n\n### Required Before Merge\n\n1. **Fix B1**: Add `AUXILIARY_SLOTS` guard in `build_render_inputs` + call `_pa.validate()` in `lifecycle_canonical.py`.\n2. **Fix B2**: Add lockstep test class covering at minimum single-provider, same-type conflict, explicit `title_generation`, and 2+ aux roles — comparing both template families.\n3. **Fix B3**: Add `TestCanonicalMultiProvider.test_bedrock_aux_emits_aws_triplet`.\n4. Address W2 (bedrock dedup state-machine gap in `hermes.env.j2`) and W3 (aux key ordering divergence between families).\n5. Fix W5 (newline sanitization in WARNING comment `_ctype`).\n",
