tion\": \"Extend test_single_provider_byte_identical_yaml_shape (or add a sibling) to also check render_hermes(...).files['.hermes/.env']: assert it contains exactly one ANTHROPIC_API_KEY line, no OPENROUTER_API_KEY, no WARNING comment, and no AWS_ lines.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py (missing test)\",\n      \"issue\": \"TestCanonicalMultiProvider has no test for multiple auxiliary roles in a single render call. test_yaml_emits_consolidated_auxiliary_block constructs only one AuxiliaryProviderInputs (role='vision'). A regression that drops the second role from the Jinja for-loop (e.g. off-by-one in aux_providers) would not be caught by any canonical test.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a canonical multi-aux test: anthropic primary + (openrouter vision, openai web_extract) auxiliaries. Assert both aux.vision and aux.web_extract keys appear in the parsed YAML and that two distinct API key lines appear in .hermes/.env.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py:146-167 / 370-389\",\n      \"issue\": \"The back-compat 'byte-identical' tests compare yaml.safe_load() field equality, not raw bytes. A regression that changes key ordering, whitespace, or adds an unexpected top-level key would pass the test as long as the three checked paths (model.provider, auxiliary.title_generation.model, set(auxiliary.keys())) remain correct. There is no snapshot fixture capturing the pre-#614 render output for true byte-regression detection.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Either store a golden fixture file under tests/fixtures/hermes-config-single-provider.yaml and assert the rendered output matches it byte-for-byte, or at minimum assert `len(parsed) == expected_top_level_key_count` to catch unexpected key additions.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_te