      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 2,\n  \"summary\": \"One blocking YAML-key injection path exists in the canonical render pipeline: `build_render_inputs` copies `role` from hosts.json into `AuxiliaryProviderInputs.role` without checking it against `AUXILIARY_SLOTS`/`VALID_ROLES`, and both templates emit that value as a bare, unquoted YAML key. The canonical sync caller (`lifecycle_canonical.py`) never calls `_pa.validate()` before `build_render_inputs`, so the guard that protects the legacy Ansible path is absent here. All other checklist items pass: `shq`/`yq` cover every secret value, WARNING comments emit only the provider type name (no key leakage), secrets are loaded exclusively from secrets.json via `_clean_secret`→truthiness, and Ansible receives providers through a structured extra-vars dict (no shell=True f-string risk).\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"blocking\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:442 + hermes-config.canonical.yaml.j2:60 + hermes-config.yaml.j2:126\",\n      \"issue\": \"YAML key injection via unvalidated `role` field. In `build_render_inputs`, the auxiliary loop (render.py:383-384) accepts any non-empty, non-'primary' role from hosts.json without checking it against `AUXILIARY_SLOTS`/`VALID_ROLES`. The comment at line 450 asserts 'Roles are unique per validate()' — but `lifecycle_canonical.py:538` calls `build_render_inputs` directly without first calling `_pa.validate()`, so the invariant is not enforced for the canonical sync path. The raw role then lands in `AuxiliaryProviderInputs.role` and is rendered as an unquoted YAML map key in both templates (`{{ _aux.role }}:` / `{{ _role }}:`). Attack: hand-edit hosts.json to set `\\\"role\\\": \\\"vision:\\\\n  malicious_key\\\"`, run `clawctl agent sync` — the canonical path will write injected YAML into the remote config.yaml. The legacy path (`sync_agent`) is mitigated because it calls `_pa.validate()` at line 1274 before building overlays.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"In `build_render_inputs`, add `from clawrium.core.provider_attachments import AUXILIARY_SLOTS` and insert `if role not in AUXILIARY_SLOTS: raise AgentConfigError(f'auxiliary provider {aux_name!r} has invalid role {role!r}; expected one of {sorted(AUXILIARY_SLOTS)}')` immediately after the `role != 'primary'` guard (render.py:385). Alternatively — or additionally — apply `| yq` / `yaml_quote` to the role key in both templates, which is safe because PyYAML and hermes' YAML loader treat quoted keys identically to bare ones for pure-alnum identifiers.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"hermes.env.j2:80-84\",\n      \"issue\": \"WARNING comment writes `_ctype` (provider type string) without sanitizing for embedded newlines. `_ctype` iterates `_conflicts` which is built from `_p.type | default('')` where `_p` is a raw entry from `config.providers` in hosts.json. If a providers.json record carries a type value containing `\\\\n`, the WARNING comment line breaks in the EnvironmentFile output, and anything after the newline is parsed as a new assignment line. Concretely: `type = 'openrouter\\\\nMALICIOUS_KEY=sk-injected'` produces `# WARNING: multiple openrouter\\\\nMALICIOUS_KEY=sk-injected providers attached...` — systemd EnvironmentFile would set `MALICIOUS_KEY` to `sk-injected providers attached...` (value with spaces is valid). Requires providers.json to carry a crafted type, which is operator-controlled, so real-world risk is low but the file is local and unprotected.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Replace `{{ _ctype }}` with `{{ _ctype | replace('\\\\n', '') | replace('\\\\r', '') | replace('\\\\x00', '') }}` in the WARNING loop. A stronger fix is to add a `_KNOWN_PROVIDER_TYPES` allowlist check in the conflict loop and skip/warn on unknown types rather than emitting them verbatim.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:374-451\",\n      \"issue\": \"No test exercises a crafted role value (`build_render_inputs` with `role='vision:\\\\n  injected'`) to confirm the function raises before the template sees it. The test file `test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py` only covers happy-path roles from `AUXILIARY_SLOTS`.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a unit test in `tests/core/test_render.py` that mocks hosts.json with an attachment carrying `role: 'vision:\\\\n  inject'` and asserts `AgentConfigError` is raised before render.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/lifecycle_canonical.py:538\",\n      \"issue\": \"The canonical sync entrypoint calls `build_render_inputs` without first normalizing and validating the attachment list, whereas `sync_agent` (lifecycle.py:1272-1274) explicitly calls `_pa.normalize` + `_pa.validate`. The missing gate is why B1 is exploitable on the canonical path and mitigated on the legacy path.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Either call `_pa.validate(normalized_attachments, agent_type)` in `lifecycle_canonical.py` before `build_render_inputs`, or add the `AUXILIARY_SLOTS` check inside `build_render_inputs` itself so the function is safe regardless of caller.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add `if role not in AUXILIARY_SLOTS: raise AgentConfigError(...)` in `build_render_inputs` at render.py:385 — one-line fix closes B1 on the canonical path without touching templates.\",\n    \"Apply `| replace('\\\\n','') | replace('\\\\r','')` to `_ctype` in hermes.env.j2 WARNING comment to close the env-line-break injection path.\",\n    \"Add `_pa.validate()` call to `lifecycle_canonical.py` before `build_render_inputs` to make the canonical and legacy paths defence-in-depth equivalent.\",\n    \"Add a negative-role test to `tests/core/test_render.py` to pin the invariant that an invalid role raises `AgentConfigError` before any template sees it.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 10,\n    \"domain\": \"hermes-multi-provider-templates\",\n    \"checklist_items_triggered\": \"B1(template-injection), W(env-comment-injection), S(test-gap)\",\n    \"checklist_items_clean\": \"secret-logging(3), sanitization-ordering(4), command-injection(5), auth-boundary(6), tunnel-state(7), dependency-hygiene(8)\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
