      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 3,\n  \"summary\": \"No blocking invariant violations. The canonical Python path (_build_provider_env_views, build_render_inputs aux loop) is well-structured: primary always registered first, creds validated before template, no KeyError paths. Four warnings hold the score at 3: a dead Python constant that creates a three-way model-map fork, a false endpoint guard for ollama auxiliaries, a primary-wins inversion in the legacy Jinja bedrock dedup, and a missing canonical-env back-compat test.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:744-749\",\n      \"issue\": \"W1 — Dead constant, three-way fork. _HERMES_DEFAULT_TITLE_GEN_MODEL is defined but never read anywhere in Python (confirmed: grep finds only the definition). The canonical YAML template (hermes-config.canonical.yaml.j2:13-18) and the legacy YAML template (hermes-config.yaml.j2:37-42) each carry their own inline copy. A model bump (e.g. haiku EOL) now requires three independent edits; forgetting the Python constant is silent but the constant accumulates staleness and misleads future reviewers into thinking it controls something.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Either delete _HERMES_DEFAULT_TITLE_GEN_MODEL entirely (it serves no runtime purpose) or make it the single source of truth by passing it as a context variable to both YAML templates and removing the inline Jinja dicts. The latter also catches template/Python map drift at test time.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:431-436\",\n      \"issue\": \"W2 — Ollama auxiliary: endpoint validated but silently discarded. build_render_inputs raises AgentConfigError when an ollama auxiliary provider has no endpoint (line 432). However AuxiliaryProviderInputs (line 118) has no endpoint field, so the validated value is thrown away immediately. The YAML template emits only {provider: 'custom', model: ...} for an ollama aux — no base_url. If the upstream hermes auxiliary slot spec genuinely does not accept base_url, then the validation is a false guard that raises a confusing user-facing error ('endpoint required in providers.json') for a value that will never be used.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Decide the intended contract. If upstream auxiliary slots do not support base_url (consistent with AGENTS.md's '{provider, model}' description), remove the endpoint guard for ollama aux to avoid the misleading error. If base_url IS needed, add endpoint: str = '' to AuxiliaryProviderInputs and emit it in the template alongside provider: 'custom'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/platform/registry/hermes/templates/hermes.env.j2:47-60\",\n      \"issue\": \"W3 — Legacy Jinja bedrock dedup: primary-wins can invert when primary has empty creds. The _seen_type_keys.update() call is nested inside {% if _aws.get('access_key') and _aws.get('secret_key') %}. If the primary bedrock attachment has empty/missing credentials, 'bedrock' is never registered in _seen_type_keys. A subsequent bedrock auxiliary then passes the '{% if _ptype not in _seen_type_keys %}' check, emits its own AWS triplet, and becomes the registered canonical entry — the auxiliary's key wins, not the primary's. The canonical Python _build_provider_env_views always registers via seen_type_keys[ptype] = key_for_compare before any credential guard, so this asymmetry is new in the legacy template. Lifecycle.py validates creds before calling Ansible, so this cannot be triggered via normal clawctl flows, but the template logic is objectively wrong and breaks primary-wins in direct/test invocations.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Mirror the Python logic: update _seen_type_keys unconditionally as soon as the type is first seen, then gate only the emission lines on credential validity. Concretely: move {% if _seen_type_keys.update({_ptype: _key_compare}) %}{% endif %} to before the inner credential-validity guard.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py:370-389\",\n      \"issue\": \"W4 — No canonical env single-provider back-compat test. test_single_provider_byte_identical_yaml_shape only pins the YAML file shape. The env template underwent a structural change: API keys are now emitted from the provider_env_views loop (new) rather than from the HERMES_INFERENCE_PROVIDER if-block (pre-#614). There is no test asserting that render_hermes with no auxiliary_providers produces the same env key set as before. A regression (e.g. blank lines from empty for-loop with trim_blocks off, or a missing HERMES_INFERENCE_PROVIDER line for an ollama-primary agent) would be invisible.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a TestCanonicalMultiProvider.test_single_provider_env_back_compat that calls render_hermes with a single-provider RenderInputs (anthropic + no auxiliary) and asserts: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY present, HERMES_INFERENCE_PROVIDER='anthropic' present, OPENROUTER_API_KEY absent, no WARNING lines.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"src/clawrium/core/render.py:382-384\",\n      \"issue\": \"S1 — role not validated against AUXILIARY_SLOTS. After the 'if not role or role == primary: continue' guard (line 383), role is accepted without checking against provider_attachments.AUXILIARY_SLOTS (which exports the canonical 9-slot tuple). An attachment record carrying role='foobar' passes all guards, constructs a valid AuxiliaryProviderInputs, and renders auxiliary.foobar: in config.yaml, which hermes silently ignores. VALID_ROLES is already exported from provider_attachments for exactly this check.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"After line 384 (role != 'primary' check), add: from clawrium.core.provider_attachments import AUXILIARY_SLOTS; if role not in AUXILIARY_SLOTS: raise AgentConfigError(f'attachment role {role!r} is not a recognised auxiliary slot. Known slots: {AUXILIARY_SLOTS}')\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Drop _HERMES_DEFAULT_TITLE_GEN_MODEL from render.py or promote it to a shared context variable passed to both YAML templates to eliminate the three-way fork.\",\n    \"Resolve the ollama auxiliary endpoint contract: either remove the false guard (if base_url is unsupported for auxiliary slots) or add endpoint field + template emission.\",\n    \"Fix hermes.env.j2 bedrock dedup: move _seen_type_keys.update() outside the credential-validity inner guard so the first bedrock entry always claims the type slot regardless of whether it has credentials.\",\n    \"Add canonical env single-provider back-compat test covering ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, HERMES_INFERENCE_PROVIDER, and absence of WARNING lines.\",\n    \"Add role validation against AUXILIARY_SLOTS in build_render_inputs to catch misconfigured attachments before they silently render and get dropped by the daemon.\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 6,\n    \"domain\": \"hermes-multi-provider-render\",\n    \"checklist_coverage\": \"all 7 items checked; items 1-5 (state machine, gateway token, layering, exception swallowing, stage routing) are not applicable to this render/template diff; items 6-7 (event emission, atomic writes) are not touched by this diff\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
